# Effect v4 MCP

Use the Effect v4 beta MCP APIs shown in `effect/unstable/ai`.

Rules:

- Keep `effect` and `@effect/*` packages pinned to the same beta version.
- Build stdio servers with `McpServer.layerStdio`, `NodeStdio.layer`, and `NodeRuntime.runMain`.
- Stdio stdout is protocol-owned. Logs and diagnostics go to stderr.
- Define MCP tools with explicit parameter and success schemas.
- Read-only tools are the default; mutating tools need explicit names, descriptions, and approval.
- Decode external JSON at the boundary before returning data through MCP tools.
- Keep pure synchronous logic pure. Use Effect for sequencing, services, failures, and runtime edges.
